pylevel package¶

Submodules¶

pylevel.data module¶

Grid module providing objects to interface with imported .mat file.

Grid module containing classes that work with saved MATLAB outputs of the Level Set Toolbox and helperOC. Much of the work is ported from helperOC into Python, with some additional convenience features added in.

pylevel.wrapper module¶

Level set wrapper providing convenience methods.

Author: Philipp Rothenhäusler, Stockholm 2020

class pylevel.wrapper.ReachableSetWrapper(label: str, from_memory: Optional[str] = None, path: Optional[str] = None, grid: Optional[pylevel.data.Grid] = None, time: Optional[list] = None, sets: Optional[Dict[float, pylevel.data.ReachableSetData]] = None, value_function: Optional[Dict[tuple, numpy.ndarray]] = None, states: Optional[dict] = None, show_config: bool = False, debug_is_enabled: bool = False)¶

Bases: object

Encapsulates convenience methods to access reachable sets.

Note:

Initialise using previously exported *.levelset using the from_memory argument or parse a label and path to initialise from a *.mat file.

ReachableSetData provides access to grid indices and their respective states using Grid, value function values or sublevel sets.

On initialisation for each discretised time step a ReachableSetData entry is added to the sets attribute.
